15.76	Mark_Oaten	Mark Oaten	Mark Oaten (born 8 March 1964 in Watford, Hertfordshire) is a former British Liberal Democrat politician. He served as the Member of Parliament (MP) for Winchester from 1997 to 2010, and was his party's Home Affairs spokesperson from 2003 to 2006. He stood for the leadership of the Liberal Democrats in the election in 2006, but withdrew from the contest when he was hit by a series of scandals which also led to his resignation as Home Affairs spokesperson. He did not run for re-election to the House of Commons at the 2010 general election.	
